description:
ManageMyHealth™ access just got easier with the Mobile App.

ManageMyHealth™ is a online service that gives you:

The freedom to manage your health needs - and that of your family anytime, anywhere
access to your medical records - view medical conditions, lab results, immunisation records, allergies, prescriptions and share health information as required with other healthcare providers
online tools to improve your health and track your progress online

•	Access and maintain both your own and your family’s medical records
•	Book appointments with your doctor/nurse
•	Request repeat prescriptions
•	View Test Results
•	Secure communication with your health professional
•	Manage your health goals, set up tasks and track results
•	Access up to date and relevant health content
•	Receive recalls, appointments and Medications reminder notifications
•	Access and maintain your MedicAlert® profile
•	Video Consultation abilities for both GP and patients.


ManageMyHealth™ is an efficient way to control and manage your health and that of your family. Even if you don’t see your doctor often, ManageMyHealth™ can help you to stay on top of your health and wellbeing.

See a doctor online or in person at a Tend clinic. Need a doctor now? See the next available GP online, nationwide.

Book a casual appointment to try Tend without switching your GP, or enrol with Tend to enjoy lower fees and ongoing care.

With Tend, you can book the next available doctor’s appointment in minutes. Get the care you need, when you need it.

Tend offers:

• Online & clinic appointments
• Same day care available nationwide
• Open 7 days until 9pm
• Instantly see the next available appointment
• See your test results
• Easily order repeat prescriptions
• View your appointment notes
• Securely message your care team
• No extra charge for evenings & weekends
• Three clinics in Auckland + more coming soon

What can we help with?

• General medical care
• Prescriptions and repeats
• Medical certificates
• ACC and injuries
• Specialist referrals
• Screenings

How Tend works:

1. Choose how you want to see a doctor
    • See the next available GP
    • Book an online appointment when it suits you
    • Book to see a doctor in person at a Tend clinic
2. For booked appointments, choose the Tend doctor, date and time that’s right for you. If you’re seeing the next available GP, you’ll be shown your estimated waiting time.
3. You’ll get a video call in the Tend app for online appointments or visit one of our Auckland medical centres for your in person appointment.
4. Prescriptions are sent to your preferred pharmacy to pick up and you can easily order repeats of your long term meds in the app.
5. Access your care team, appointment notes and test results any time through the Tend app

Who can use Tend?

• Auckland residents can use all of Tend’s services as a casual or enrolled patient.
• Everywhere else in NZ can only see the next available GP online as a casual patient.

Is Tend safe?
The safety and protection of your data is paramount to us. We’re a registered primary care services provider subject to all healthcare laws and regulations, with stringent and comprehensive patient privacy policy and data protection measures to ensure your information is safe and secure. Download the Tend app today. Your home for health.

Learn more at www.tend.nz

Modernise your healthcare experience. The Doctors app easily connects you to your general practice team. The Doctors has been developed after listening to patients and general practices about what they really need in a patient app. It’s healthcare that’s centred around you. 
 
Download The Doctors app to: 
- Access your health summary including lab results, prescribed medications, diagnosed conditions, and immunisation history 
- See consultation notes from previous appointments 
- Book an appointment with your preferred practitioner, or select the next available slot 
- Book an appointment for someone else 
- Book and attend video consults 
- Request repeats of previously prescribed medications 
- Message your GP team 
- Receive reminder notifications for appointments  
- Track the status and receive notifications on your repeat medication request 
- Pay for your medication requests or appointments 
- Login using passcode or touch/facial recognition 
- Choose to share your medical information with other healthcare providers if required 
 
To use The Doctors app you will need an invite code from your general practice team. 
 
Powered by Centrik.

The Astra Radiology Patient app is used by patients to securely access medical imaging results and to request an appointment at one of The Astra Radiology clinics throughout Auckland.

This app will allow you, the patient, to view and easily share results with your family and/or other health professionals. Once your scan is complete and your results are ready to view, an SMS/text message link will be sent to your mobile device or email, for you to activate your account and set a secure password.

Providing the referring doctor has granted access, most results will be available approximately 7 days after the examination has been reported by an Astra Radiologist.

Please note, your referring doctor will have access to your images and report as soon as they are available. You should always return to your doctor to discuss your results.

Once you have activated your account, a notification will be sent to view any future results via the app. This gives you the ability to keep a copy of your personal radiology results on file, which you can access anywhere, anytime.

The ‘Request an Appointment’ feature allows you to arrange a booking at one of our radiology clinics. Simply select the type of imaging service required, choose your preferred location, time and date, then upload a photo of the referral form provided to you by your doctor. Once submitted, a member of our staff will contact you to book and confirm the appointment.

If you require assistance with the Astra Radiology Patient app, please submit a ticket at https://astra.zed.link

Emergency Q reduces crowding in Hospital Emergency Departments (EDs) by creating a live connection between patients, EDs and Urgent Care Clinics (UCCs).  

It empowers patients suited to primary care by providing them with a live view of forecast wait times for non-emergency patients at participating hospital EDs and UCCs.

This app is for New Zealand Blood Service blood donors only. It features everything you need to book your next blood donation appointment in New Zealand.

∞ Use the app to book your next whole blood or plasma appointment (Platelet donors can use the app to access their details and view their appointments).
∞ Search for a place to donate.
∞ Look up your donation history.
∞ Book, reschedule or cancel an appointment.

Tell us what you think
We’ve listened to your feedback from our previous versions to refine this app, but we know it can always be better. That’s why we want you to download it, use it and give us some feedback. In return, we’ll do our best to make it even better! Download the app for free and give it a whirl, then let us know what you think at info@nzblood.co.nz. Thank you for helping to save lives.

Terms of Use
By downloading and using NZ Blood Service Donor App, you agree to the terms of use in the app.

Heidi is the best way to capture clinical notes on the go. Whether you’re on the ward, in theatres, or out in the community, Heidi keeps up — so you can focus on patients, not paperwork.

Transcribe in real time, dictate naturally, and make light note edits anywhere you work. Everything syncs securely to your account, ready on your computer when you are.

Heidi even works offline. If your connection drops, transcription and edits continue without interruption. Notes sync automatically once you’re reconnected. Sessions pause and resume if a call comes in, so you never lose your place.

You can also capture and upload photos directly into your notes, adding context in the moment. And with Face ID or PIN login, everything stays fast and secure.

Heidi is trusted worldwide:

- 8 million hours returned to clinicians every year

- 2 million consults supported every week

- 200+ specialties covered, from GPs to allied health, hospitals to rural care

Why it matters:

- More time with patients, less time on admin

- Fewer errors, with AI reviewed and refined by clinicians

- Less burnout, no more late-night notes

- Revenue-ready, with billing, coding, and follow-ups

- Safe and compliant: HIPAA, GDPR, PIPEDA, NHS, APP, ISO 27001



Join thousands of clinicians already using Heidi to move care forward.


Terms of Use: heidihealth.com/legal/heidi-scribe-terms-of-use
Privacy Policy: heidihealth.com/legal/privacy-policy

Huckleberry is your all-in-one parenting partner, proudly trusted by 5+ million families worldwide. 

From baby tracker to personalized guidance, our award-winning app helps you navigate sleep, feeding, milestones, and everything in between. Backed by a team of pediatric experts and powered by smart tools, Huckleberry supports each family’s unique journey. We turn restless nights into restful routines, making more space for everyday magic.

TRUSTED SLEEP GUIDANCE & TRACKING

Your baby's sleep and daily rhythms are unique. Our comprehensive baby tracker helps you understand their natural patterns while providing expert sleep guidance every step of the way. From breastfeeding to nappies, our newborn tracker gives you peace of mind in those early days and beyond.

SWEETSPOT®: YOUR SLEEP TIMING COMPANION

A most-loved feature that predicts your baby's ideal nap times with remarkable accuracy. No more guessing about sleep windows or watching for tired cues—SweetSpot® learns your child's unique rhythms to suggest optimal sleep times. Available with Plus and Premium memberships.

BERRY: 24/7 PARENTING GUIDANCE 

Instant parenting backup that adapts to what you need, when you need it. Using expert-vetted and AI-powered guidance, Berry can work through the messiness of parenting with you. You can solve challenges, get reassurance, and easily track multiple things at once—all in one AI chat. No matter the moment or mood, you always have backup.

FREE APP FEATURES

• Simple, one-touch baby tracker for sleep, nappy changes, feedings, pumping, growth, potty training, activities and medicine
• Complete breastfeeding timer with tracking for both sides
• Sleep summaries and history, plus average sleep totals
• Track multiple children with individual profiles
• Reminders when it’s time for medication, feedings, and more
• Sync with multiple caregivers across different devices

PLUS MEMBERSHIP

• All free features, and:
• SweetSpot®:  Predicts the ideal time for sleep (2+ months)
• Schedule Creator: Plan age-appropriate sleep schedules
• Insights: Data-driven tips and miniplans for sleep, feedings, and milestones (0-17 months)
• Enhanced Reports: Discover your child’s trends
• AI Logging: Track your child’s day through text, voice message, or photo

PREMIUM MEMBERSHIP

• Everything in Plus, and:
• Berry: 24/7 guidance with our expert-vetted AI chat
• Custom Sleep Plans: expert-designed plans built for your child, with weekly progress check-ins and ongoing support as they grow 

GENTLE, EVIDENCE-BASED APPROACH

Our sleep guidance never requires "crying it out." Instead, we blend trusted sleep science with gentle, family-centered solutions that respect your parenting style. Every recommendation is made for your family's needs and comfort level.

PERSONALIZED PARENTING SUPPORT

• Expert newborn tracker tools and analytics
• Get custom sleep schedules based on your baby's age and patterns
• Science-backed guidance for common sleep challenges
• Navigate sleep regressions with confidence
• Receive timely recommendations as your baby grows
• Help your newborn develop healthy sleep habits from day one

AWARD-WINNING RESULTS

The Huckleberry baby tracker app ranked #1 in the iOS medical category globally. Today, we help families across 179 countries achieve better sleep. Up to 93% of families using our baby sleep tracking report improved sleep patterns.

Whether you're navigating newborn sleep, infant solids or toddler milestones, Huckleberry provides the tools and guidance your family needs to flourish.

Terms of Use: https://www.huckleberrycare.com/terms-of-use
Privacy Policy: https://www.huckleberrycare.com/privacy-policy

Diabetes goes where you go, now your glucose readings can too, with the Dexcom ONE+ Continuous Glucose Monitoring (CGM) system and mobile app†.  
With the Dexcom ONE+ mobile app†, users can access their real-time glucose readings at a glance and set customisable alerts that can help warn of highs and lows, all with no finger pricks* or scanning. Discuss with your healthcare professional how you should use the information displayed on the Dexcom ONE+ to help manage your diabetes.
 
The Dexcom ONE+ mobile app† has been designed with enhanced features to help in the management of diabetes: 
•	The app-led onboarding allows users get started in a few clicks only. 
•	Share your glucose data with up to 10 followers who can monitor your glucose data and trends on their compatible smart device with the Dexcom Follow app. Share and Follow functions require an internet connection. 
•	Key diabetes metrics displayed in the Clarity Card section of the mobile app, so that users can see both real-time and retrospective glucose data.** 
•	Event logging where users can track activities like meal intake, exercise sessions and insulin injections, helping them better understand their glucose patterns.1 
•	Alerts to notify users 12-hours before the end of a sensor session, so you can change your sensor when it’s convenient for you.1  
 
Apple Watch: 
•	View your glucose information, trend graph, and alerts right from your wrist with the Dexcom ONE+ Apple Watch app. Watches require compatible smart device to use app. 
 
Learn more at Dexcom.com. 
 
This app is only for use with the Dexcom ONE+ Continuous Glucose Monitoring System. 
 
*If your glucose alerts and readings from the Dexcom ONE+ do not match symptoms or expectations, use a blood glucose meter to make diabetes treatment decisions 
† Smart device sold separately. For a list of compatible devices, visit www.dexcom.com/compatibility. 
**An internet connection is required for patients to send their glucose data to Dexcom Clarity via a compatible smart device: dexcom.com/compatibility. 
1 Dexcom ONE+ User Guide, 2023.

Download the latest version and explore everything Bountiful has to offer.

The FreeStyle LibreLink app is approved for use with FreeStyle Libre and FreeStyle Libre 2 system sensors. You can check your glucose by scanning your sensor with your phone. Now FreeStyle Libre 2 system sensor users can get automatic glucose readings in the FreeStyle LibreLink app, updated every minute, and also receive alarms when your glucose is low or high. [1][2]

You can use the FreeStyle LibreLink app to:

* View your current glucose reading, trend arrow and glucose history
* Receive low or high glucose alarms with FreeStyle Libre 2 system sensors [2]
* Add notes to track your food, insulin use and exercise
* See reports, such as Time in Range and Daily Patterns
* Share your data with your doctor and family, with your permission [3]

SMARTPHONE COMPATIBILITY
Compatibility may vary between phones and operating systems. Learn more about compatible phones at http://FreeStyleLibre.com.

USING YOUR APP AND READER WITH THE SAME SENSOR
Alarms can only be issued on your FreeStyle Libre 2 reader or your phone (not both). To receive alarms on your phone, you must start the sensor with the app. To receive alarms on your FreeStyle Libre 2 reader, you must start the sensor with your reader. Once the sensor has been started with the reader, you can also scan that sensor with your phone.

Remember that the app and reader do not share data with each other. For complete information on a device, scan your sensor every eight hours with that device; otherwise, your reports will not include all your data. You can upload and view data from all of your devices on LibreView.com.

APP INFORMATION
FreeStyle LibreLink is intended for measuring glucose levels in people with diabetes when used with a sensor. For more information on how to use FreeStyle LibreLink, refer to the User’s Manual, which can be accessed through the app. If you require a printed User’s Manual, contact Abbott Diabetes Care Customer Support.

Consult a healthcare professional to confirm if this product is right for you or if you have questions about how to use this product to make treatment decisions.

Learn more at http://FreeStyleLibre.com.

[1] If you are using the FreeStyle LibreLink app, you must also have access to a blood glucose monitoring system, as the app does not provide one.  

[2] Alarms that you receive do not include your glucose reading, so you must scan your sensor to check your glucose.

[3] Use of FreeStyle LibreLink and LibreLinkUp requires registration with LibreView.

The sensor housing, FreeStyle, Libre, and related brand marks are marks of Abbott. Other trademarks are the property of their respective owners.

For additional legal notices and terms of use, go to http://FreeStyleLibre.com.

========

To resolve any technical or Customer Service issues that you are having with a FreeStyle Libre product, please contact FreeStyle Libre Customer Service directly.

﻿The BeMore app lets you control your hearing aids directly from your mobile device. You can change programs, and make simple or more advanced sound adjustments and save them as favorites. The app helps you learn what you can do and how to do it. It can even help you find your hearing aids if you lose them. Last, but not least, you can have your hearing care professional update your hearing aid programs and send you new hearing aid software without taking a trip to the clinic.

BeMore mobile device compatibility:
Please consult the BeMore app website for up-to-date compatibility information: www.gnhearing.com/guides/app-support

Use the BeMore app to: 
•	Enjoy optimization anywhere with online services: Request help with your hearing aid settings from your hearing care professional and receive new settings and software updates. 
•	Adjust volume settings on your hearing aids
•	Mute your hearing aids
•	Adjust volume of your streaming accessories
•	Adjust speech focus as well as noise and wind-noise levels with Sound Enhancer (feature availability depends on your hearing aid model and the fitting by your hearing care professional)
•	Change manual and streamer programs
•	Edit and personalize program names 
•	Adjust treble, middle and bass tones to your preferences
•	Save your preferred settings as a Favorite – you can even tag to a location
•	Monitor the battery status of your rechargeable hearing aids
•	Help locate lost or misplaced hearing aids
•	Tinnitus manager: Adjust sound variation and frequency of the Tinnitus Sound Generator. Select Nature Sounds (feature availability depends on your hearing aid model and the fitting by your hearing care professional)

For more information please visit the support website via the link in the app store.

* Over 3 million skin checks 
SkinVision is a medical service that provides an immediate risk assessment.
Skin checks with our clinically validated technology are affordable and potentially covered by your health insurance provider. You can buy a single risk assessment or purchase unlimited checks to effectively monitor your moles for 3 or 12 months (no subscription).

You can use some features of SkinVision for free including our risk profile and skin type quizzes, storing images of your moles and accessing UV information in your area.
Our checks use an algorithm to assess your mole or skin spot for suspicious signs. Our service is quality assured by our team of dermatology experts. Our users have received more than 3.5 million risk assessments.

The SkinVision app is a regulated medical device with European CE marking. We care about your privacy and are ISO certified for information security and the quality management system. SkinVision is trusted by insurance companies worldwide for skin health. SkinVision has partnerships with leading health insurers, dermatology clinics and research universities in the United Kingdom, Australia, Germany, the Netherlands, and New Zealand.

WHY SKINVISION?
Dermatologists recommend checking your skin spots at least every 3 months.
Monitoring spots can help you to identify suspicious signs at an early stage. By using SkinVision, you can:
- Receive an immediate risk indication for your mole or skin spot.
- Store your photos to help monitor changes over time and easily share them with your doctor.

CONNECT WITH SKINVISION
Instagram - https://www.instagram.com/sknvsn/
If you have any questions or comments about the service, please contact us at info@skinvision.com.

Terms and Conditions - https://skinvision.com/terms

Please note: The SkinVision Service augments already existing self-assessment techniques of skin lesions. It does not provide a diagnosis and is not an alternative to healthcare professionals. The SkinVision Service is not intended for use on persons under the age of 18 years old.

Experience hearing like never before with the Amplifon App — your gateway to better hearing health and smarter control of your hearing aids.

Whether you're just starting your hearing care journey or already using compatible hearing aids, the Amplifon app offers everything you need for a seamless, empowering experience. Take a free hearing screening test, explore a wide range of expert content on hearing health, and stay connected to your personal clinician — all in one place.

Smart Hearing Aid Management
Pair your compatible Bluetooth® hearing aids and take full control — adjust programs, volume, and background noise levels with ease.

Personalized Insights
Monitor your hearing aid usage and track your progress to get the most out of your devices.

Easy Appointment Booking
Schedule visits with your preferred clinic quickly and conveniently.

Step-by-Step Guidance
Learn how to use and care for your hearing aids with tailored tutorials and daily maintenance tips.

Direct Support Access
Get in touch with customer service whenever you need expert help.

Chat privately with a doctor at the touch of a button. 

No appointments or bookings are required. Just start a secure chat at any time.

Get fast consults, prescriptions, advice & treatment from your phone anywhere in New Zealand.

Use Well Revolution doctors, or if your GP clinic recommended Well Revolution, you will find them in the app too.

- Well Revolution doctors are available 7 days a week until late.
- Consults with Well Revolution doctors cost $49 between 8 am and 6 pm every day including weekends.
- If your GP is in the app, their usual fees apply.

Prescriptions are sent instantly in the app to your choice of pharmacy.

Use Well Revolution

- for same-day access to your own GP, or 
- connect with a Well Revolution doctor if you don’t have a GP, can’t get to one or when your GP isn't available.

How Well Revolution Works

1. Start a chat anytime. No need to book an appointment. 
2. Chat privately with the doctor. 
3. Send your prescription directly to your choice of pharmacy.
4. Send sick notes directly to your employer.

Who can use Well Revolution?

- Well Revolution is open to everyone in New Zealand. 
- There are no monthly fees. Pay only after a consult with the doctor.

We can help with

- General medical advice and treatment
- Prescriptions
- Medical certificates, sick notes

Download the app and chat with a doctor now.

Have a question or need help?
Start a live support chat with us. Tap App Support in the Well Revolution app or visit wellrevolution.co.nz 

--------------------

FAQs

How do chat consultations work?
Start a consult with one tap and send a private and secure message to the doctor. Your message is sent directly to the doctor and you will be notified as soon as they respond. If needed, the doctor can start a live audio or video call with you. You can send text and voice messages, make voice and video calls, and share images and documents, all from inside the app.

Do I need to enrol?
Enrolment is not required. Well Revolution does not change your GP. If your enrolled clinic is using the app, you’ll find them there too.

How do I make an appointment?
No appointment is needed. Start a private chat at any time.

What does it cost?
Well Revolution Doctors cost
- $49 between 8 am and 6 pm, 7 days per week and 
- $79 for all other hours, including public holidays.
- If your GP is on the app, their usual fees apply. 
- You will see any fees before you start a consult.

How do prescriptions work?
The doctor creates and sends paperless prescriptions for you in the app. Then you choose how you want it. Select your favourite or nearest pharmacy for the most convenient pick-up location.

Is Well Revolution safe?
When you use Well Revolution, you are trusting us with your information. We take your privacy seriously. This app and our service are subject to all healthcare and privacy laws and regulations in New Zealand. All doctors on Well Revolution are professional, qualified and licensed in New Zealand. Our strict privacy policies and data protection methods are designed to keep your information safe and secure.

What can’t Well Revolution help with? *
We’re not yet able to help with
- Restricted medications, controlled drugs, opiates
- ACC claims
- Lab and radiology requests

*If your enrolled GP is in the app, they will be able to help you.

What doctors are on Well Revolution?
You can use Well Revolution doctors at any time, or if your GP clinic recommended Well Revolution, you will find them in the app too. If your own GP or clinic is not on the app or if they’re not available, you can connect with a Well Revolution doctor to get the care you need right away. All doctors on Well Revolution are exclusively in New Zealand.

Who are the Well Revolution Doctors?
You will see their profiles in the app. All Well Revolution doctors are qualified and registered New Zealand General Practitioners. They can help with many common medical conditions. Head to well.as/treat to learn more.

Always consult your doctor to orient yourself in terms of contraction frequency and duration.

CareSens Air



The CareSens Air CGMS (Continuous Glucose Monitoring System) enables continuous monitoring of blood glucose levels when used with the CareSens Air sensor and app. For more information on how to use CareSens Air, please refer to the user manual available within the app. Printed copies of the user manual can be obtained by contacting the Pharmaco customer satisfaction centre at 1800 114 610, 0800 458267.

The CareSens Air Continuous Glucose Monitoring System (CareSens Air CGM System) is indicated for the continuous monitoring of blood glucose levels by measuring glucose in the interstitial fluid in individuals with diabetes mellitus aged 18 years and older. The CareSens Air CGM System is intended to replace standard blood glucose testing for diabetes treatment decisions, unless otherwise specified. The system helps detect trends such as hyperglycaemia and hypoglycaemia by providing continuous glucose data, manage changes in glucose levels through trend detection and pattern tracking, and assist in diagnosis and treatment when consulting healthcare professionals.



The CareSens Air app provides the following features:

- Real-time blood glucose measurements recorded every 5 minutes
- Blood glucose trend arrows and statistics
- Alerts for low/high glucose levels, rapid changes, and sensor replacement
- Event memos for blood glucose levels, ketone levels, insulin, oral medication, meals, exercise, etc.
- Data sharing with the Sens365 app or website
- Compatibility with smartphones may vary depending on the operating system. Information on compatible smartphones, additional legal notices, and terms of use can be found on the website (https://caresensair.com)
- For technical support or customer service enquiries, please contact the Pharmaco customer satisfaction centre at 1800 114 610, 0800 458267.


"The instructions for use of the CareSens Air CGM System are supplied in electronic form" https://caresensair.com/download
